title: From Queen To Tanu Weds Manu: Top 7 Movies Of Kangana Ranaut
text: All Image Credit: IMDb This iconic film follows Rani, a woman who embarks on a solo honeymoon after her wedding is called off. Kangana's portrayal of a strong, independent woman earned her widespread acclaim and a National Award. As a drug-addicted supermodel, Kangana's performance stole the spotlight for her fierce and bossy attitude, winning her a National Award for Best Supporting Actress. A sequel to Tanu Weds Manu, where Kangana plays a double role. Her portrayal of both Tanu and the Haryanvi athlete Kusum was lauded, earning her another National Award. In her debut film, Kangana played a troubled lover caught in a love triangle with a gangster and a singer. Her powerful performance set the stage for her successful career. Kangana both starred in and co-directed this historical biopic about Rani Lakshmibai, earning praise for her strong and commanding performance. In this crime drama set in 1970s Mumbai, Kangana plays an actress involved with a gangster. Despite a supporting role, her performance was praised. Kangana played the role of a free-spirited woman with a gambling addiction with her charming yet complex portrayal.
